ome cases. Additionally, we find that of the GR deviations we\nconsider, the residuals test is only able to detect extreme deviations from GR\nthat no longer look like binary black hole coalescences in GR. The\nreconstruction comparison shows more promise for detecting relatively small GR\ndeviations in an unmodeled framework, at least for high-mass systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Sep 2021 22:09:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 1 Feb 2022 17:49:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-23"}
