ral determinants: beta-strand breaking, steric hindrance and/or charge\nrepulsion, all implying the impairment of interdomain contacts. All available\nevidence suggests that the rearrangement of the protein global architecture\ntriggers a furin-independent aggregation of the protein, supporting the\nexistence of a non-canonical pathway of gelsolin amyloidosis pathogenesis.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Sep 2021 10:10:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-16"}
